The course covers following topics: general cellular characteristics of the yeast cell, yeast metabolism, genetic information in yeast, yeast genetics, yeast molecular techniques, genetic screens, conditional mutants, yeast life cycle, cell cycle, yeast life span and ageing, pathogenic yeasts, biotechnology applications.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give overview about modern yeast molecular biology and to introduce the basic methodology of the yeast molecular genetics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the student will: - know the characteristics of yeast cell and metabolism; - analyse and compare the life and cell cycles of different yeasts (budding yeast, fission yeast, pathogenic yeasts); - gain knowledge in the field of various yeast genetics methods and their working principles; - be able to use the genetic nomenclature correctly; - use the yeast genetic databases without assistance, be able to critically interpret the collected information; - obtain skills in different methods used in yeast genetics.
